% gen250: contrast facts for the generic "difference between X and Y" frame.
difference_between(ram, rom, "RAM is fast volatile working memory; ROM is non-volatile memory for firmware or fixed data").
difference_between(climate, weather, "Climate is the long-term pattern; weather is short-term local conditions").
difference_between(cement, concrete, "Cement is a binder; concrete is cement mixed with sand, gravel, and water").
difference_between(jam, marmalade, "Jam is a fruit preserve; marmalade is usually a citrus preserve with peel").
difference_between(sea, ocean, "An ocean is a vast named body of salt water; a sea is smaller or partly enclosed").
difference_between(crocodile, alligator, "Crocodiles usually have V-shaped snouts; alligators have broader U-shaped snouts").
difference_between(rabbit, hare, "Hares are generally larger, faster, and born furred; rabbits are smaller and burrow").
difference_between(frog, toad, "Frogs usually have smooth moist skin and jump; toads have drier bumpy skin and crawl more").
difference_between(turtle, tortoise, "Tortoises are land turtles; many turtles live in or near water").
difference_between(leopard, cheetah, "Cheetahs are built for speed with tear marks; leopards are stronger climbers with rosettes").
difference_between(monkey, ape, "Apes generally lack tails and have larger brains; most monkeys have tails").
difference_between(bee, wasp, "Bees are usually fuzzier pollen collectors; wasps are smoother and often predatory").
difference_between(butterfly, moth, "Butterflies usually fly by day with clubbed antennae; moths often fly at night").
difference_between(crow, raven, "Ravens are larger with wedge-shaped tails and deeper calls; crows are smaller").
difference_between(affect, effect, "Affect is usually a verb meaning influence; effect is usually a noun meaning result").
difference_between(its, it_is, "Its means belonging to it; it's is a contraction of it is or it has").
difference_between(there, their, "There points to a place or existence; their means belonging to them").
difference_between(england, uk, "England is one country; the UK also includes Scotland, Wales, and Northern Ireland").
difference_between(england, united_kingdom, "England is one country; the UK also includes Scotland, Wales, and Northern Ireland").
difference_between(holland, netherlands, "The Netherlands is the country; Holland is a region often used informally for it").
difference_between(left, right_politics, "Left politics stresses equality and public provision; right politics stresses tradition or markets").

